  "local_port": 43500,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I want to activate my old whatsapp but I'm over seas and have the old number?",
  "response": "Activating your old WhatsApp account while overseas and still using your old number is possible, but it depends on whether you can receive SMS or calls on that number. Here's how you can proceed:\n\n### 1. **Ensure Your Old Number is Active**\n   - If your old number is still active and can receive SMS or calls, WhatsApp will send a verification code to that number during activation.\n   - If the number is no longer active, you\u2019ll need to contact your mobile carrier to reactivate it temporarily or port it to a new SIM.\n\n### 2. **Download WhatsApp**\n   - Download WhatsApp from the App Store (iOS) or Google Play Store (Android).\n\n### 3. **Verify Your Old Number**\n   - Open WhatsApp and enter your old phone number.\n   - WhatsApp will send a verification code via SMS to that number.\n   - If you can\u2019t receive SMS (e.g., no roaming), tap **\"Call Me\"** to receive the code via a phone call.\n\n### 4. **Use WhatsApp with the Old Number**\n   - Once you receive the code and verify your number, your account with the old number will be reactivated.\n   - Your chat history should be restored if you previously backed it up.\n\n### 5. **If You Can\u2019t Access the Old Number**\n   - If your old number is inactive and you can\u2019t receive the verification code, you\u2019ll need to contact your mobile carrier to reactivate it or port it to a new SIM.\n   - Alternatively, if you\u2019ve lost access to the number permanently, you\u2019ll need to use a new number and back up your old chats if possible.\n\n### 6. **To Backup and Restore Chats**\n   - If you have a backup (Google Drive for Android or iCloud for iOS), you can restore your chat history during the setup process.\n   - If you\u2019re switching from Android to iOS or vice versa, you may need to use third-party tools to transfer chats.\n\nLet me know if you need help with any specific step!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
